HEADWORD: chutzpah
<hw>chutzpah</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Yiddish <ets>khutzpa</ets>.]</ety> <def>aggressive boldness or
unmitigated effrontery; gall; <as>as, he had the <ex>chutzpah</ex> to
question my decision</as>.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled <asp>hutzpa</asp>,
and <asp>hutzpah</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> audacity, audaciousness.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

